            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">13. A 23-year-old man presents to the rheumatology clinic with lower back and hip pain. These have been occurring every day for the past two months. Pain and stiffness are worse in the mornings. He also mentions that his right heel has been hurting. He is previously fit and well, but had occasions of lower back pain when he was a teenager. His symptoms have stopped him from playing tennis. Recent blood tests organized by his GP have shown a raised C-reactive protein (CRP) and erythrocyte sedimentation rate (ESR). What is the most appropriate treatment?</p>"
